    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="109"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.154/3266</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Under Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Stettinius</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-11">October 11,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Warren<note n="9" xml:id="d109fn9">Avra M. Warren, Ambassador in the
                        Dominican Republic.</note> came in to pay his respects. He stated that the
                    Inter-American Highway<note n="10" xml:id="d109fn10">Caribbean land-water
                        route.</note> financed with Lend-Lease funds was not going well. He also
                    informed me of the changed conditions resulting in there now being very little
                    reason for the road, and that Haiti and the Dominican Republic are not
                    interested. He feels that unless there are impelling military reasons for its
                    construction it should not proceed.</p>
                <p>I have informed Mr. Bernhard Knollenberg of Lend-Lease of this.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
